AGI - The Hungarian court has accepted, after several actions rejected in the past, the defence requesting the domiciles for Ilaria Salis> in Budapest.&nbsp;Salis will pay by 24 May >, the date of the next hearing of the process in which it is charged to have assaulted some neo-Nazi protesters >, the deposit of 40 thousand euros requested by the Second Instance of Budapest to obtain them. It is what AGI learns from legal sources.&nbsp;Salis has three months to pay bail, according to what is reported in the measure that has accepted the appeal of its lawyers by establishing that there are no longer the requirements to keep it closed. It is likely therefore that it will turn to the trial no longer with the chains at the feet and led on a leash by the prison police, an image that had aroused a stir and indignation. The domiciles will have to hold the electronic bracelet > and will be able to leave the house where it will only be with the judge's ok.
&nbsp;
Reactions
<h3> The father, the Minister of Justice and Foreign Affairs, no aid
"We pay the Minister of Justice and Foreign Affairs to work for us, we have not seen any concrete activities to solve the problem of Ilaria by these two ministries": is the vent of the father of Ilaria Salis, Roberto, on Gedi channels, after the granting of house arrests in Hungary to the daughter.
"I don't have pebbles in my shoes, but the big gravel, the one that is used for concrete, I have bloody feet," said Roberto Salis, complaining that his complaints are "remained in the drawers". "Italian citizens are sick of having to beg institutions to act, institutions are at the service of citizens."
<h3>Nordio, satisfaction for news</h3>
"Soddisfaction" for the news of the "concession of house arrests" in Ilaria Salis. To express it was the Minister of Justice Carlo Nordio, in the Chamber Hall, during the question time.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h3>M5s, government bringing home
"We are happy that Ilaria Salis can finally leave prison and domicile. It's the end of a nightmare that lasted too long. Now we expect the Italian government to move to allow our citizens to pay the penalty in Italy." The 5 Star Movement of Chamber and Senate Foreign Commissions declare this.
&nbsp;
<h3>Avs, nomination has been chosen </h3>
"Candidare Ilaria Salis in the Avs lists for Europeans was the right choice. The demonstration that it was necessary to light the spotlight on the story so that a result in compliance with the rule of law was reached. What refused to do the Meloni government for months not to disturb his friend Orban, or simply because the right the decision on Salis had already issued it. Happy for his next scarceness, no shame for our executive." On Facebook, the group leader of the Green Alliance and Left Peppe De Cristofaro, president of the mixed group of Palazzo Madama.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"This result is mainly due to the tenacity and determination of the family - says Angelo Bonelli and Nicola Fratoianni - and of all those who instead of being silent have fought and will continue to do so for the rights of Ilaria and all of us. We are happy and even more convinced of our choice of running Ilaria in our lists".<br> "Now after this first victory, so important for you and all of us, we want to bring it back to Italy and then to Brussels as a European Parliament because the question of respect for rights in Europe becomes a fully political issue" conclude.&nbsp;
